The (PEA)2MA3Sb2Br9 perovskite sensor was placed in air, and a voltage from 0 to 10 V was applied to record the background current. After that, the (PEA)2MA3Sb2Br9 sensor was placed in an alcohol environment, and after waiting for 30 s, a voltage of 0 to 10 V was applied again, and its current–voltage (I–V) characteristics were recorded. Figure 1b sketches the experimental set up. In alcohol response measurement, the definition of the normalized responsivity ratio (R) of the sensor is as follows:1R=ΔII0=I-I0I0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
